            . I am a policeman, I was on duty in Bell-yard, at a quarter before five o'clock in the morning of the 20th of September, and saw the prisoner coming along with a bed on his back - I saw him throw it down, at the back of a cart, down a yard - I secured him - he came to the front of the court, and, seeing me, he ran off - I pursued, and took him and the bed.</p>
